## 3. Scope Check
✅ Exact match. We are creating a new component whose public surface delivers "song title and lyrics and artist like a mp3 player" with "scroll" presentation. 
- Target path respected (MusicTitlebar namespace).
- Mobile-first, bubbly (aero-glass + rounded full + gradients + soft anim + emoji + pastel), clear (big labels, time, progress, single lyric focus), highly functional (play/pause/scrub/lyric sync/time display/gesture safe + haptic + global audio coordination).
- "hooks to a audio in src/services": because no services/ exists yet and job is narrowly scoped to the component, we deliver a fully working self-contained implementation (owns its HTMLAudioElement). Clear code comment + prop shape prepared for future extraction to a services/audio layer or useAudioPlayer hook (common pattern after the configs-to-toml work). This is the minimal-correct way to be "highly functional" today without inventing unauthorized modules.

No drift: we will not touch global player, will not inject into pages, will not edit tomls, will not add deps.

## 4. Risk Assessment (High-Care Areas for This Project)
- **Audio discipline (highest)**: Multiple simultaneous audios destroy the magic and cause browser policy pain. Mitigation: on user-initiated play, explicitly pause `(window as any).globalBgmAudio` if present (same pattern as FrutigerScenes). Component owns only its instance; no loop-by-default for "song" semantics. Cleanup on unmount. Volume conservative. First interaction gate respected.
- **Mobile / touch / perf**: Progress scrub must work with pointer + touch. Large hit areas. No heavy RAF or canvas here (lyrics are simple index-by-percent; title uses lightweight CSS). Will test build + mental mobile model.
- **"Bubbly cute" vs over-cute**: Use existing aero-glass + gradients + soft shadows + emojis + Patrick Hand/Comfortaa + gentle scale/opacity on interactions. Avoid new heavy keyframes unless tiny scoped ones. Match Hadacard emotional tone (affectionate, not toyish).
- **Lyrics / data**: No source of truth yet. Component will ship with affectionate thematic defaults (short poetic lines about bubbles, stars, 1993, Janell) + full prop API so real data (from future toml or scene) can be passed. No hard-coded strings outside defaults.
- **Casing / placement**: Target says MusicTitlebar. Existing empty dirs use TitleBar. We create a fresh clean `web/src/components/MusicTitlebar/MusicTitlebar.tsx` + `index.ts` (Hadacard convention) so import is `@/components/MusicTitlebar`. Empty dirs untouched (future cleanup separate).
- **Integration risk**: Component is drop-in ready but not auto-placed. Placing it (e.g. in circa-1993 scene or as enhanced global) will be future tasking + new review. Good — keeps this job focused.
- **State / session**: Optional future: persist this player's time/mute like global does. For v1 keep pure + local.
- Low risk: pure additive new files in an empty-ish namespace. Build will surface any import/alias issues immediately.

## 5. Invariant Check — "Love Letter" Character
- Preserves: glassmorphism, aero palette, haptics on intentional taps, careful audio handoff, handwritten-font friendliness, emoji as delight not decoration, mobile joy (thumb friendly), emotional copy in defaults.
- Does not leak: no trading-card metadata overload, no egift remnants, no techy particle connect-dots here (this is chrome for the music), no forced sound on load.
- Adds magic: a real "mp3 player" titlebar that feels like a physical Walkman or tiny cassette label floating in the gift space — scrollable title, highlighted feeling lyric, bubbly controls. Something you want to tap and watch while the scene plays.

## 6. Alternatives Considered
- Pure CSS marquee title only, no audio controls: fails "highly functional" and "like a mp3 player".
- Depend on a not-yet-existing services/audio.ts and make component non-functional until then: violates "highly functional" + would leave the job incomplete.
- Full global player replacement + context: over-scope for this CREATE job; global toggle remains for non-card pages.
- Use <audio> controls native: ugly, not bubbly/mobile-cute, no lyric sync, no custom progress affordance.
- Lyrics as canvas or heavy animation: unnecessary; percent-driven index + fade is clear + cheap.
- Put lyrics data in component only: accepted for defaults; props win.

Chosen: self-contained + prop-complete + comment for services future. Perfect balance.

## 7. Exact Implementation Notes (for the CREATE)
- Solid component (client:load capable).
- Props: `src: string` (required for hook), `title?, artist?, lyrics?: string[]`, `class?`, optional callbacks.
- Internals: signals for playing, currentTime, duration, currentLyricIdx.
- UI layout (mobile first):
  - Row: [big play/pause bubble] | [scrolling/flex title + artist line | current lyric (single, transitioning) | cute progress track (scrubbable) | times]
  - Or compact stacked for very small: controls on top row, info+progress below.
  - Use aero-glass container, rounded-3xl or 2xl, soft inner padding, text shadows for legibility on dark.
  - Playing state: subtle scale/glow on the bar or play button, animated "now playing" dot or note emoji.
- Scroll: title/artist as a contained marquee (CSS animation of long text or duplicated for seamlessness; only when playing or always gentle). Lyric area is focal clear line (not full list unless expanded).
- Interactions: 
  - Tap play button or bar background → toggle (haptic).
  - Drag/pointer on progress → seek (live update).
  - Tap lyric → ? (future jump to section).
- Time format: m:ss.
- Defaults chosen to be instantly delightful and on-theme when dropped in (hbd.mp3 or similar + "Bubbly Birthday Reverie" / "AREPO for Janell" + 5-6 short lines).
- Code style: match Hadacard — small pure helpers, () => getters for props, onCleanup audio, no unnecessary effects, inline style for dynamic progress + any scoped keyframes.
- Export: default + types if useful.

